     Home page

   French    English

Permanent members


Students



   The Research laboratory Géomatériaux et Environnement (LGE) of
   University Paris-Est Marne-la-Vallée is recognized by the Ministry of
   Higher Education and Research (EA 4508) and includes 15
   teacher-researchers, 3 engineers and 1 administrative.


   The laboratory's activities are divided into two scientific issues. The
   first one concerns the study of the interactions between pollutants
   and water and / or soil. The second one  concerns the study of the
   formation and evolution of geological, historic and environmental
   geomaterials.  As member of the ERASMUS MUNDUS ETeCoS3 doctoral
   program, the laboratory welcomes every year between 3 and 4 PhD
   students in the field of environmental technologies. The laboratory
   offers a scholarship in the field of geomaterials.

